Reverse the String

Question: You are given a string A of size N.
Return the string A after reversing the string word by word.

Question Link: https://www.interviewbit.com/problems/reverse-the-string/?study_plan=study-plan-1-week&/

Intuition: Splitting string based on spaces; using StringBuilder to recreate the string using append and trimming the final string.

Special mention: Edge cases considering the whitspaces in the begining and ending of string

Java Solution:

public class Solution {
    public String solve(String A) {
    
        String[] splitedString = A.split("\\s+");
        StringBuilder output = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = splitedString.length - 1; i >=0 ; i--) {
                output.append(splitedString[i]).append(" ");
        }
        return output.toString().trim();

    }
}
